# OOP Principles

This project applies all four core Object-Oriented Programming principles throughout its design.

---

## 1. Abstraction

**Definition:** Hide implementation details and expose only what is necessary through abstract classes and interfaces.

### Where We Use It

#### `Card` — Abstract Class
```java
public abstract class Card {
    protected String color;
    protected String type;

    // Concrete method — shared by all cards
    public boolean canPlayOn(Card other) {
        return this.color.equals("WILD")
            || this.color.equals(other.color)
            || this.type.equals(other.type);
    }

    // Abstract method — each card type MUST implement this
    public abstract void applyEffect(GameState state);
}
```
The game engine calls `card.applyEffect(state)` without knowing what the card actually does. The detail is hidden inside each subclass.

#### `Player` — Abstract Class
```java
public abstract class Player {
    // Abstract — subclass decides HOW to take a turn
    public abstract Card takeTurn(GameState state);

    // Abstract — subclass decides HOW to pick a color
    public abstract String chooseColor();
}
```

#### `PlayStrategy` — Interface
```java
public interface PlayStrategy {
    Card chooseCard(List<Card> playableCards, GameState state);
}
```

#### `GameObserver` — Interface
```java
public interface GameObserver {
    void onCardPlayed(Player player, Card card);
    void onTurnChanged(Player nextPlayer);
    void onGameEnd(Player winner);
    // ...
}
```

