## 2. Inheritance

**Definition:** A child class acquires properties and behaviors of its parent class, promoting code reuse.

### Card Hierarchy
```
Card  (abstract)
├── NumberCard    → inherits color, type, canPlayOn()
├── ActionCard    → inherits color, type, canPlayOn()
└── WildCard      → inherits color, type; overrides canPlayOn()
```

```java
// NumberCard inherits everything from Card
// Only adds value and its own applyEffect()
public class NumberCard extends Card {
    private int value;

    public NumberCard(String color, int value) {
        super(color, String.valueOf(value)); // calls Card constructor
        this.value = value;
    }

    @Override
    public void applyEffect(GameState state) {
        state.advanceTurn(); // just advance — no special effect
    }
}
```

### Player Hierarchy
```
Player  (abstract)
├── HumanPlayer   → inherits hand, drawCards(), getPlayableCards()
└── AIPlayer      → inherits hand, drawCards(), getPlayableCards()
```

```java
// Both HumanPlayer and AIPlayer get these for free from Player:
// - hand management (addCard, removeCard, getHand)
// - drawCards(n)
// - getPlayableCards(topCard)
// They only need to implement takeTurn() and chooseColor()
```

**Code Reuse:** Over 60% of Player's functionality is written once in the parent class and shared by both subclasses.

