## 4. Encapsulation

**Definition:** Bundle data (fields) and methods together, and restrict direct access to the internal state using access modifiers.

### Example 1 — Card fields are protected
```java
public abstract class Card {
    protected String color;  // subclasses can read it
    protected String type;   // but outside code cannot set it directly

    public String getColor() { return color; }       // controlled read
    public void setColor(String color) { this.color = color; } // controlled write
}
```

### Example 2 — Deck constructor is private (Singleton)
```java
public class Deck {
    private static Deck instance;   // hidden
    private Queue<Card> drawPile;   // hidden
    private List<Card> discardPile; // hidden

    private Deck() { ... }  // PRIVATE — cannot call new Deck() from outside

    public static Deck getInstance() { ... }  // only way to access the deck
    public Card draw() { ... }                // controlled operation
    public void discard(Card card) { ... }    // controlled operation
}
```

### Example 3 — GameState controls all mutations
```java
public class GameState {
    private int currentIndex;  // hidden — outside code cannot jump to any turn
    private int direction;     // hidden — cannot flip without going through method

    // Controlled mutations only — no public fields
    public void advanceTurn()     { currentIndex = nextIndex(1); }
    public void skipNextPlayer()  { currentIndex = nextIndex(2); }
    public void reverseDirection(){ direction = -direction; }
}
```

### Summary Table

| Class | Private Fields | Controlled Access |
|-------|---------------|-------------------|
| `Card` | `color`, `type` | `getColor()`, `setColor()` |
| `Deck` | `drawPile`, `discardPile`, `instance` | `draw()`, `discard()`, `getInstance()` |
| `Player` | `name`, `hand` | `getHand()`, `drawCards()`, `addCard()` |
| `GameState` | `currentIndex`, `direction`, `gameOver` | `advanceTurn()`, `reverseDirection()` |
